Korea University.UniDescription: Encourage the holistic growth of active intellectual and spiritual attributes in students, nurture their capacity for insightful study and their commitment to their subsequent professional lives, and foster open-minded leadership skills within them, enabling them to contribute to the advancement of humanity and the international community

Yonsei University.UniDescription: Yonsei University serves as the 'alma mater' of all arts and sciences to nurture leaders who will contribute to the Korean and international society, in the ecumenical spirit of Christian teaching epitomized in its motto of “truth and freedom.” Yonseians will inherit mankind’s cultural legacy, and lead academic development through creativity and critical thinking. We will also serve others with an open heart, and contribute to the prosperity of humankind. With these missions, we Yonseians will demonstrate our leadership to realize the Yonsei spirit globally.

Seoul National University.UniDescription: Fosters practical and cooperative skills through the implementation of a convergence, “L-shaped” education system that lowers the barriers between different majors and invites in-depth interdisciplinary discussions. Enables students to explore various perspectives through student-directed education programs and interdisciplinary courses such as 'Interdisciplinary Approaches.'

The University Of Manchester.UniDescription: The welcoming, accessible and multicultural environment that is the city of Manchester provides the ideal base for your time studying in the UK. Choose Manchester and you'll put yourself ahead of the competition when the time comes to begin your career. With an award-winning careers service and courses built with your employability in mind, it's no surprise that 94% of our graduates go straight into jobs or further study. If you're interested in starting a business in the UK, the Masood Entrepreneurship Centre offers resources and support for student-led start-ups. We're part of the prestigious Russell Group of universities and our research and teaching quality is recognised across the globe, but our support for international students is just as important to us. We'll help you at all stages, from before you apply to when you arrive - and you'll be supported at all times while you're here. We also encourage you to become the best you can be by participating in Stellify - a journey through Manchester's most transformational experiences, giving you a unique opportunity to experience true personal and professional growth during your time with us. We'll give you an experience that will prepare you for a lifetime of achievement.

KTH Royal Institute Of Technology.UniDescription: Since its founding in 1827, KTH Royal Institute of Technology in Stockholm has grown to become one of Europe's leading technical and engineering universities, as well as a key centre of intellectual talent and innovation. We are Sweden's largest technical research and learning institution and home to students, researchers and faculty from around the world dedicated to advancing knowledge.

Chalmers University Of Technology.UniDescription: Over the past two hundred years, technological progress has made a decisive contribution to a better life for humankind. However, it is that same technological development that is in many ways responsible for the serious situation our planet now finds itself in. Chalmers must therefore focus even more on the transition that is needed for sustainable change. The vision combines that focus with a clearly outspoken ambition to improve. To be better in order to make a bigger difference. We will provide education and research at the highest international level that also effectively benefits both people and the planet.

ETH Zurich.SemOneWindow: Mid September to End December (excluding examinations)
ETH Zurich.SemTwoWindow: Mid February to End May/June (excluding examinations)
ETH Zurich.UniDescription: Whether in the natural sciences, engineering, mathematics, architecture or management, ETH Zurich degree programmes convey knowledge with a long half-​life and enable their graduates to address fundamental issues and challenges.

Uppsala University.UniDescription: The mission of Uppsala University is to gain and disseminate knowledge for the benefit of humankind and for a better world. The University rests on the idea and fundamental premise that investments in education and research contribute to a better future. The University aims to offer an inspiring and well-functioning physical, social and cultural environment. Uppsala University contributes to development and innovation locally and nationally and is an active party in the pursuit of sustainable social development. Collaboration with the wider community is a natural, integral part of such research and contributes - directly or indirectly - to solutions to the sustainability challenges facing society.

University Of Stockholm.UniDescription: Stockholm University offers a wide range of education in close interaction with research. Collaboration helps make Stockholm University's expertise and results accessible and promotes quality in education and life-long learning. Here you can find information about our organisation, collaborations and other facts about Stockholm University.

Lund University.UniDescription: Lund University was founded in 1666 and is consistently ranked among the top 100 universities in the world. The University has approximately 46 000 students and 8 600 employees based in Lund, Helsingborg, Malmö and Ljungbyhed. We are united in our efforts to understand, explain and improve our world and the human condition.

National Tsing Hua University.UniDescription: National Tsing Hua University is a research university with a long and proud tradition. Since the re-establishment in Hsinchu in 1956, the university has been known for her excellent academic programmes as well as her spacious verdant campus. NTHU initially began in Taiwan with nuclear sciences studies, and gradually expanded to include general sciences and engineering; in the past twenty years, the social sciences and humanities, life sciences, information sciences, and management sciences were added.

The University Of Western Australia.UniDescription: We have the immense privilege of sitting on the sacred soil where Western Australian kaartdijin, or knowledge, began. It has been a place to gather and learn for tens of thousands of years, with stories and lessons shared from generation to generation of the world’s oldest continuous culture.

The University Of Sydney.UniDescription: We acknowledge the tradition of custodianship and law of the Country on which the University of Sydney campuses stand. We pay our respects to those who have cared and continue to care for Country.

National Taiwan University.UniDescription: The National Taiwan University (NTU) was established in 1945 with five colleges - College of Liberal Arts and Law, College of Medicine College of Science, College of Agriculture and College of Engineering. Today, NTU is a comprehensive university with eleven colleges offering a wide range of up-to-date disciplines and numerous research centres.

National Cheng Kung University.UniDescription: National Cheng Kung University (NCKU) was founded in 1931. It is a leading comprehensive university in Taiwan with more than sixty departments in nine colleges covering the fields of Bioscience and Biotechnology, Electrical Engineering and Computer Science, Engineering, Liberal Arts, Management, Medicine, Planning and Design, Sciences and Social Sciences. The University is committed to enhancing its reputation through abundant resources, strong alumni support, and cooperative ventures with the Tainan Science-based Industrial Park. NCKU has been selected as the Prominent Research University in Taiwan and voted Industry's Most Favorable University.

National Chiao Tung University.UniDescription: The National Yang Ming Chiao Tung University (NYCU) was officially formed on 1 February 2021 with the merger of National Chiao Tung University and National Yang-Ming University, two top universities in Taiwan. National Yang-Ming University was noted for its expertise in Medicine, Life Sciences and Biotechnology while National Chiao Tung University was renowned for its excellence in engineering, computing, and science. NYCU is a comprehensive university with more than 1,400 faculty and researchers and over 17,000 students, consisting of a broad spectrum of colleges, including engineering, medicine, nursing, dentistry, life sciences, social sciences, and humanities.

Georgetown University, Washington D.C..UniDescription: We're a leading research university with a heart. Founded in the decade that the U.S. Constitution was signed, we're the nation's oldest Catholic and Jesuit university. Today we're a forward-looking, diverse community devoted to social justice, restless inquiry and respect for each person's individual needs and talents.

University Of Guelph.UniDescription: U of G offers more than 80 undergrad programs, more than 100 graduate and post-doctoral study programs, co-op education in a wide variety of disciplines, support for international students, continuing education for lifelong learners, diploma programs and access to a unique form of higher education at the University of Guelph-Humber. We'll help you make the choices - we'll help you explore the possibilities. Our community is tailored for students, and that difference is noticeable from the first moment you get in touch.

University Of Birmingham.UniDescription: We are a member of the elite Russell Group of UK universities. Birmingham is the first Russell Group, and global top 100 university to establish a campus in Dubai. Birmingham has one of the largest international student communities in the UK, with over 10,000 students from 150 countries.

University Of Oslo.UniDescription: The university has approximately 27,700 students and employs around 6,000 people. Its faculties include (Lutheran) theology (with the Lutheran Church of Norway having been Norway's state church since 1536), law, medicine, humanities, mathematics, natural sciences, social sciences, dentistry, and education.

University College Dublin.UniDescription: UCD is one of Europe's leading research-intensive universities; an environment where undergraduate education, masters and PhD training, research, innovation and community engagement form a dynamic spectrum of activity.

The University Of British Columbia.UniDescription: The University of British Columbia is a global centre for teaching, learning and research, consistently ranked among the top 20 public universities in the world. UBC embraces innovation and transforms ideas into action.

King's College London.UniDescription: King's College London is one of the top 35 universities in the world (QS World University Rankings 2022) and among the oldest in England. King's has more than 29,600 students (of whom nearly 11,700 are graduate students) from some 150 countries worldwide, and some 8,000 staff.

Monash University.UniDescription: Monash is a modern, global, research-intensive university, delivering education and research excellence in Australia and across the Indo-Pacific. We're making a positive impact on today's global challenges - whether that's by mitigating climate change, easing geopolitical insecurity or fostering healthy communities.

Concordia University.UniDescription: Located in the vibrant and multicultural city of Montreal, Concordia is the top-ranked university in North America founded within the last 50 years and annually registers some 51,000 students through its innovative approach to experiential learning and cross-functional research.

Western University.UniDescription: Western University ranks as one of Canada's top research universities. From fundamental to applied knowledge, Western discoveries benefit economic, social, health and cultural development in Canada and around the world. Western University ranks as one of Canada's top research universities.

The Hong Kong Polytechnic University.UniDescription: The Hong Kong Polytechnic University (PolyU) is the largest publicly funded tertiary institution in Hong Kong in terms of student population. It has an international community with over 1,000 international students on campus from over 40 countries and over 1,200 academic staff, many who are recruited globally. The "Jockey Club Innovation Tower" designed by Zaha Hadid can facilitate further inter-disciplinary research and design education, reinforcing Hong Kong as Asia's design hub.

The University of Hong Kong.UniDescription: The University of Hong Kong (HKU), founded in 1911, is the oldest tertiary institution in Hong Kong and one of the best comprehensive universities in Asia. The campus is situated on the north-western slopes of Hong Kong Island between 50 to 150 metres above sea level and overlooks the wide sweep of Victoria Harbour. Since its establishment in 1911, it has undertaken the mission of providing a holistic education, developing the intellectual and personal strengths of its students.

City University of Hong Kong.UniDescription: City University of Hong Kong (CityU) offers professional education that prepares its students for the challenges and exciting opportunities opening up in Hong Kong, the Asia-Pacific region and throughout the world in business, science and engineering, energy and environment, law, creative media and social sciences.

The Chinese University of Hong Kong.UniDescription: As the second oldest university in Hong Kong, The Chinese University of Hong Kong (CUHK) is a leading comprehensive research university with a global vision and a mission to combine tradition with modernity, and to bring together China and the West.

Kyushu University.SemOneWindow: Early April to Early August; Early April to End July (for JTW)
Kyushu University.SemTwoWindow: Early October to Mid February; Early October to End February (for JTW)
Kyushu University.UniDescription: Kyushu University is a comprehensive university located in Fukuoka, Japan. It is the 4th oldest university in Japan and one of the most prestigious universities in Japan.

Waseda University.UniDescription: Waseda University offers a range of programs to undergraduate exchange students. Undergraduate students will be enrolled in regular courses offered by 14 undergraduate schools. English courses are offered by various schools including the School of Political Sciences and Economics, the School of Commerce, the Contemporary Japanese Studies Program, the School of International Liberal Studies (SILS), the School of Fundamental Science and Engineering, the School of Creative Science and Engineering, and the School of Advanced Science and Engineering. Students may also take Japanese courses offered by the Center for Japanese Language. The School of Fundamental Science and Engineering, School of Creative Science and Engineering and School of Advanced Science and Engineering only accept students in their third year or above. SILS offers a one-year program to international students and participants can take courses with regular (4 year) SILS students in this program. It offers courses on a wide range of topics including Asian culture, society, politics, economy, geography, arts and literature. All courses are conducted in English. Students participating in SILS are required to take both intensive Japanese Courses and Lecture Courses in each semester.

Tokyo Institute of Technology.UniDescription: Tokyo Institute of Technology offers the Young Scientist Exchange Program (YSEP) and Academic Cooperation Agreement Program (ACAP) to exchange students. YSEP is a one-semester program for students who have completed at least two and a half years of study at their undergraduate study. ACAP is a program for undergraduate students in their 2nd year or above. The school offers programs in the School of Science, School of Engineering, and School of Bioscience and Biotechnology. The duration of the exchange can be one semester or a full year, and module mapping is required before departure. Students are expected to attend all mandatory examinations at the host university, and Japanese language proficiency is not required. Students must apply through their home faculty in NUS between September and June, and must have completed at least one year of study at NUS for ACAP or two and a half years for YSEP upon application. Accommodation is provided, but limited, and visa applications must be completed immediately upon receipt of official offer letter/email from the host university. Students are encouraged to purchase comprehensive travel insurance for the full duration of their stay abroad, including personal travel within/outside Japan.

University of Tokyo.SemOneWindow: April to August (Term S1 and S2)
University of Tokyo.SemTwoWindow: September to March (Term A1, A2 and *W)
University of Tokyo.UniDescription: U Tokyo offers the University-wide Student Exchange Programme (USTEP) – Type U programme to undergraduate exchange students. The programme offers various courses, conducted in English and/or Japanese by the various Faculties & Colleges in U Tokyo.

Kyoto University.UniDescription: Kyoto University offers the following programmes to exchange students: Kyoto University International Education Programme (KUINEP), Kyoto University General Exchange Programme (GE Programme)

Vilnius University.UniDescription: Vilnius University is a comprehensive university with over 20,000 students located in Vilnius, Lithuania. It is the oldest and largest university in the country, founded in 1579. The university has faculties in a wide range of academic disciplines, including Humanities, Mathematics and Informatics, Natural Sciences, Social Sciences, Law, and Medicine.

Utrecht University, The Netherlands.UniDescription: Utrecht University is a host university for the Student Exchange Programme (SEP). Students can study for one semester at the University College Utrecht or the University Medical Center Utrecht. Exchange students are welcome to read courses from any faculty except the Faculty of Medicine, Faculty of Veterinary Medicine, UCU, University College Roosevelt (UCR), and Centrum voor Onderwijs en Leren. The academic prerequisites and restrictions vary depending on the faculty or department that you apply for. Online course catalogue available at: https://www.uu.nl/en/education/exchange-and-visiting-students/courseinformation

Eindhoven University of Technology.UniDescription: Eindhoven University of Technology is a technical university located in Eindhoven, Netherlands.

Norwegian University of Science and Tech.SemOneWindow: Middle of August to Late December
Norwegian University of Science and Tech.SemTwoWindow: Early January to Middle of June

The College of William and Mary.UniDescription: The College of William and Mary is a comprehensive university and suitable for FASS, FoS, and SoC students.

AARHUS UNIVERSITY, DENMARK.UniDescription: Aarhus University is a research-intensive university located in Aarhus, Denmark. It is a highly regarded institution that offers a wide range of courses across various faculties. It has a rich academic history and is known for its high-quality research and teaching standards.

The University of Sheffield.UniDescription: Located in the city of Sheffield, South Yorkshire, the University of Sheffield is a research university with a global reputation for excellence. The University is a red brick university and a member of the Russell Group: one of the 24 leading UK universities for research and teaching.

Tulane University.UniDescription: Tulane University is a comprehensive university with schools of Science and Engineering, Liberal Arts, and Public Health and Tropical Medicine.
